Etymology. Although there is no specific dedication to Johanna Bonne-Wepster, there is no doubt that this species was named in her honour (
Kitzmiller, 1982
). Mrs Bonne-Wepster and her husband Prof. Cornelis Bonne, both Dutch, jointly and separately published the results of fieldwork they conducted in Suriname and the East Indies.

